{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:sirach.35",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 35,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 35 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.35.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:1",
      "text": "He that keepeth the law, multiplieth offerings.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.35.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:2",
      "text": "It is a wholesome sacrifice to take heed to the commandments, and to depart from all iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.35.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:3",
      "text": "And to depart from injustice, is to offer a propitiatory sacrifice for injustices, and a begging of pardon for sins.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.35.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:4",
      "text": "He shall return thanks, that offereth fine flour: and he that doth mercy, offereth sacrifice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.35.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:5",
      "text": "To depart from iniquity is that which pleaseth the Lord, and to depart from injustice, is an entreaty for sins.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.35.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:6",
      "text": "Thou shalt not appear empty in the sight of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.35.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:7",
      "text": "For all these things are to be done because of the commandment of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.35.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:8",
      "text": "The oblation of the just maketh the altar fat, and is an odour of sweetness in the sight of the most High.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.35.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:9",
      "text": "The sacrifice of the just is acceptable, and the Lord will not forget the memorial thereof.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.35.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:10",
      "text": "Give glory to God with a good heart: and diminish not the firstfruits of thy hands.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.35.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:11",
      "text": "In every gift shew a cheerful countenance, and sanctify thy tithes with joy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.35.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:12",
      "text": "Give to the most High according to what he hath given to thee, and with a good eye do according to the ability of thy hands:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.35.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:13",
      "text": "For the Lord maketh recompense, and will give thee seven times as much.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.35.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:14",
      "text": "Do not offer wicked gifts, for such he will not receive.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.35.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:15",
      "text": "And look not upon an unjust sacrifice, for the Lord is judge, and there is not with him respect of person.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.35.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:16",
      "text": "The Lord will not accept any person against a poor man, and he will hear the prayer of him that is wronged.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.35.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:17",
      "text": "He will not despise the prayers of the fatherless: nor the widow, when she poureth out her complaint.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.35.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:18",
      "text": "Do not the widow's tears run down the cheek, and her cry against him that causeth them to fall?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.35.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:19",
      "text": "For from the cheek they go up even to heaven, and the Lord that heareth will not be delighted with them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.35.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:20",
      "text": "He that adoreth God with joy, shall be accepted, and his prayer shall approach even to the clouds.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.35.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:21",
      "text": "The prayer of him that humbleth himself, shall pierce the clouds: and till it come nigh he will not be comforted: and he will not depart till the most High behold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.35.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:22",
      "text": "And the Lord will not be slack, but will judge for the just, and will do judgment: and the Almighty will not have patience with them, that he may crush their back:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.35.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:23",
      "text": "And he will repay vengeance to the Gentiles, till he have taken away the multitude of the proud, and broken the sceptres of the unjust,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.35.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:24",
      "text": "Till he have rendered to men according to their deeds: and according to the works of Adam, and according to his presumption,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.35.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:25",
      "text": "Till he have judged the cause of his people, and he shall delight the just with his mercy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.35.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:26",
      "text": "The mercy of God is beautiful in the time of affliction, as a cloud of rain in the time of drought.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
